{"word":"ἀργαλέος","slug":"ἀργαλέος","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<el><b>ἀργαλέος</b></el> <br/><b><a href='S:Etymology'>Etym.</a> </b><a href='S:ἄλγος'><el>ἄλγος</el></a>, as if <el>ἀλγαλέος</el>\n<p/><div class='li750'><b>1. </b><i>painful, troublous, grievous</i>, <a href='S:Latin'>Lat.</a> <el>gravis</el>, <b><a href='S:Iliad'>Il.</a></b>, <b><a href='S:Aristophanes'>Ar.</a></b>:— <el>ἀργαλέον ἐστί</el>, <a href='S:cum'>c.</a> <a href='S:dative'>dat.</a> et <a href='S:infinitive'>inf.</a>, 'tis <i>difficult</i> to do a thing, <b><a href='S:Homer'>Hom.</a></b>; rarely <a href='S:cum'>c.</a> <a href='S:accusative'>acc.</a> et <a href='S:infinitive'>inf.</a>, <b><a href='S:Iliad'>Il.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li750'><b>2. </b>of persons, <i>troublesome</i>, <b><a href='S:Theognis'>Theogn.</a></b>, <b><a href='S:Aristophanes'>Ar.</a></b><p/></div>"}]}